            <h2>Seminars/Workshops (Available On Request)</h2>
            <h3>Women’s Self Defense</h3>
            <img src="_images/women.jpg" alt="" class="inline right">
            <p>For our women’s self defense courses, you will learn the fastest methods to defend yourself in any scenario It is is designed to meet the self-protection needs of Women, teenagers, and girls. We provide you with the necessary tools to make quick intelligent decisions, and learn how to disengage from violent encounters and escape.  Our training programs are specially structured to empower you with the physical skills to protect yourself as well as empower you to face your fears and overcome them.</p>
            <p>These tactics ensure a rapid response using gross motor skills and basic awareness skills to give you the best chance of survival in a time of crisis. The curriculum was designed specifically to be learned in a short amount of time.  Gain confidence in yourself and in your abilities as you learn to protect yourself. Techniques and subjects will include situational awareness, verbal commands, body language and distance control. For striking, you will learn the use of vital strikes and improvised weapons to escape a violent encounter. You will be trained in our Escape to Gain Safety (ETGS) program.</p>
            <p>We regularly teach seminars and workshops throughout the CSRA. Be sure to contact us to find out when the next Women’s Self Defense program is coming to your area. If you are a martial arts school owner, Student Activity Director or other interested party and would like to host a Women’s Self Defense or Rape Prevention Seminar, please do not hesitate to call or email us today.</p>
            <h3>Military JKD and SpecOPS Kali</h3>
            <p>Military JKD and SpecOPS Kali is currently being taught to Team ONE Network as their Law Enforcement and Military Hand-to-hand combat system. Contemporary JKD has been taught to Navy SEALS, FBI, CIA and DOD officers. The curriculum focuses on the force continuum, verbalizations, hand-to-hand combat, the disarming and use of weapons/improvised weapons, defense strategy, multiple opponent scenarios and the use of lethal force if necessary.</p>
            <h3>JKD for LEO / Police Defense Tactics</h3>
            <p>Elite members and instructors of the PFS and PDTI system receive world-class tactics field tested by law enforcement, SWAT, SF military, Secret Service, NAVY Seals, and FBI. The ranks of PDTI are designed to guide members through a natural progression of learning that is based on flinch responses, natural biological and psychological tendencies, as well as compliance to the force continuum.</p>
            <p>The foundation of PDTI training is introduction to hand-to-hand combat essentials, control tactics, verbal and physiological commands, and weapons defense. As a member progresses, the detail and nature of the training will compound and build, developing the member into a well rounded, optimally trained, prepared asset to any military, SF military, SWAT, EMT or law enforcement unit. Subjects include locking, control tactics, pain manipulation, baton, defensive postures, pressure points, ground avoidance and escapes with an emphasis on non-lethal force.</p>
